Package player

Class Player

java.lang.Object
javafx.scene.Node
javafx.scene.image.ImageView
player.Character
player.Player
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget, Jumpable, Movable
public class Player extends Character implements Movable, Jumpable
Player class is a class that can be used to initialize player in gameplay state (the player that you control). This class implements Moveable and Jumpable which are Marker interfaces. This class also has its own SpriteAnimation imported from SpriteAnimationClass and lots of boolean value to check which animation the player object should be showing.
Author:
Mos

  • Constructor Details

    • Player

      public Player​(javafx.scene.image.Image image, int velocityX, int velocityY, int translateX, int translateY)
      Player's constructor simply pass first three parameter to super constructor. The last two parameter is use to setFitWidth and fitHeight (since a Player's object is also an ImageView's object)
      Parameters:
      image - Used to set player's image
      velocityX - Used to set player's horizontal velocity
      velocityY - Used to set player's vertical velocity
      translateX - Used to set blocks positionX
      translateY - Used to set blocks positionY
